 A Russian military expert has claimed that Putin’s forces have destroyed an artificial island just off the southern Ukrainian coast, where he alleged that British troops had been stationed. Both the claim that British soldiers were present on the island during the time of the alleged strike, if ever, cannot be verified, nor can the actual destruction of the island. It appears to be the latest attempt by Russian state media, albeit not from the more mainstream propagandistic sites, to peddle misinformation about what is happening in Ukraine as Putin’s Armed Forces struggle to make significant territorial gains on the frontlines. MORE TO FOLLOW...   